    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/17451</id>
    <published>2012-08-24T00:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-08-24T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/carriage-of-dangerous-goods-authorisations"/>
    <title>Carriage of dangerous goods authorisations</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Under Regulation 9(2) (rail) and 12(1) (roads) of The Carriage of Dangerous Goods and Use of Transportable Pressure Equipment Regulations 2009 (as amended), the Secretary of State for Transport, may issue written authorisations that allow for deviations from the requirements of  European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road (&lt;abbr title="European agreement about international transport of hazardous goods by road"&gt;ADR&lt;/abbr&gt;) and Regulations concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Rail (&lt;abbr title="Regulations concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Rail"&gt;RID&lt;/abbr&gt;). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These authorisations carry conditions and time limits, and apply to carriage within GB only; they can be withdrawn by the competent authority at any time by means of a written notice.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
