    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-carriage-of-dangerous-goods-approved-derogations-and-transitional-provisions"/>
    <title>The carriage of dangerous goods: approved derogations and transitional provisions</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;h2 id="summary"&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;‘The carriage of dangerous goods: approved derogations and transitional provisions’ is a legally binding document. It sets out the circumstances in which a particular type of carriage or the carriage of dangerous goods in a particular scenario is exempt in the UK from requirements and prohibitions. It also gives detail where alternative requirements and prohibitions to apply. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be read in conjunction with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2009/1348/contents/made"&gt;The Carriage of Dangerous Goods and Use of Transportable Pressure Equipment Regulations 2009 (CDG 2009)&lt;/a&gt; as amended for Great Britain&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/title/the%20carriage%20of%20dangerous%20goods?page=1"&gt;The Carriage of Dangerous Goods and Use of Transportable Pressure Equipment Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010&lt;/a&gt; as amended&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/nisr/2010/59/contents/made"&gt;The Carriage of Explosives Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-documents"&gt;Related documents&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.dft.gov.uk/topics/freight/dangerous-goods/security/"&gt;Security of dangerous goods in transport&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
